----
# ptui / psh-tui
- micro-sized tui lib in pure sh
## Functions
- hline
  -- create line
  ---- $1 length
  ---- $2/- char to use
  ---- $3 indentation
  ---- $4 text to print AROUND
  ---- $5 indentation before
  ---- $6 indentation after
  -- does NOT create a new line
- vline
  -- create vertical line 
  ---- $1 tall
  ---- $2 indentation
  ---- $3/| char to use
  ---- $4 text to print
  ---- $5 line to print on
  ---- $6 indentation before
  -- creates new line
- dvline
  -- creates 2 lines 
  ---- $1 tall
  ---- $2 indentation
  ---- $3/| char to use 
  ---- $4 apart
  ---- $5 text to print AROUND
  ---- $6 lint to print on
  ---- $7 indetation before
  -- indents after based on `$(($2-${#5}-${7:-0})))` 
  -- creates new line
- mvline
  -- same as dvline but for $1 lines
  -- still WIP
- rec 
  -- makes a fucking rectangle
  ---- $1 indentation
  ---- $2 wide (-1)
  ---- $3 tall (-1)
  ---- $4/- char to use for top and bottom
  ---- $5/| char to use for sides
  ---- $6 disable + corners if 0

